Job Description:
The future of energy is digitised, decarbonised and localised. At Smartest Energy, we need revolutionary thinkers to help our customers make the most of this new landscape, thinking differently to find smart solutions to complex problems.

Formed in 2001, we’re an agile business driven by entrepreneurial thinking. As a subsidiary of the Marubeni Corporation, we also have strong investment and infrastructure behind us. We have three offices in the UK, one in the US and another in Australia. Further expansion is planned for 2022 and beyond which means global career opportunities for you, with plenty of potential to explore new markets.

Flexibility is vital to success in our business and many of our staff work flexibly in many different ways, including part-time, compressed hours, remotely or a mix of remote/office. Please talk to us about what flexibility means to you and don’t let anything stop you from applying.

When you join our Team, you will have the opportunity to contribute and make an impact every single day.

Overview

You will lead and manage data related activities across the organisation to ensure data is available, of a high quality, relevant, accurate and reliable, and can be leveraged to drive business outcomes.
Working closely with business and IT teams, the Data & Analytics Manager will identify data & analytics requirements, design/implement practical fit for purpose solutions, and support staff with all data and analytics-based activities.

In this role, you will be involved with the following:

Identify data and analytics requirements across all functions of the business;
Work with stakeholders, business and IT teams to prioritize collected requirements, develop business cases and project implementation plans;
Lead projects to implement appropriate solutions ((both technical and non-technical);
Document processes for data collection, processing, modelling and analysis, including data flow diagrams and data dictionaries;
Develop tools and dashboards to track the health and quality of data;
Troubleshoot data issues, facilitate the issue/root cause determination, develop solution options and work with required teams to implement the fix;
Support other key business and IT projects as the Data lead;
Ensure compliance with regulatory and privacy laws, data retention and information classification guidelines.

To be successful in this role, you are likely to have the following skills/experience:

Bachelor's degree in business, computer science, computer engineering, electrical engineering, system analysis or a related field of study, or equivalent experience;
Experience in the Energy industry;
Demonstrated experience working in Data Management, Data Governance or related areas;
Demonstrated experience in designing and implementing data management solutions;
Excellent knowledge of current technologies and developments within the ‘Big Data’ field;
Knowledge of wholesale energy markets, retail supply offtake, regional sales markets as well as market rules and regulations;
Knowledge of Microsoft Azure, MySQL, Python, Java, C# and other programming languages and platforms;
Knowledge of business ecosystems, SaaS, infrastructure as a service (IaaS), platform as a service (PaaS), SOA, APIs, open data, microservices, event-driven IT and predictive analytics;
Knowledge of business engineering principles and processes;
Familiarity with basic graphical modeling approaches, tools and model repositories.

What else do we offer?

A genuine commitment to smarter working – we recognise your work/life balance matters;
Excellent compensation package;
Open and inclusive work culture to bring your best self to work;
Career development and learning opportunity;
Role can be based in Sydney or Melbourne;

Diversity

Celebrating our inclusive and diverse culture is core to what we do. We value everybody irrespective of background, disability, religion, gender identity, sexuality or ethnicity.

We know that for our business to thrive we need diverse talent with a range of backgrounds, skills and capabilities in each of the countries in which we operate. We view diversity as one of the key enablers that helps our business to grow.

